    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1822"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1822">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 871.001F37/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Vopicka</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 35.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department acknowledges the receipt of your
                    despatch No. 143, Roumanian Series, of October 24 last, enclosing a letter
                    addressed to the President by His Majesty Ferdinand in which he announced the
                    death on October 10, 1914, of His Majesty Carol I and his accession to the
                    throne of Roumania.</p>
                <p>The Department encloses herewith, with office copy, a letter addressed by the
                    President to His Majesty Ferdinand, King of Roumania, acknowledging the letter
                    transmitted with your despatch of the 24th of October.</p>
                <p>You will forward the copy to the Foreign Office and deliver the original in the
                    manner most agreeable to His Majesty.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to King
                                <persName type="to">Ferdinand</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Great and Good Friend</hi>: I have received the letter
                        of the 17th of October last in which Your Majesty informed me of the death,
                        on the 10th of the same month, of your beloved uncle, His Majesty Carol I,
                        and your accession to the throne of Roumania.</p>
                    <p>In expressing my sincere and heartfelt sympathy for Your Majesty and the
                        people of Roumania in their bereavement, I must at the same time give
                        utterance to the satisfaction with which I received the announcement that
                        you had ascended the throne, and assure Your Majesty that your wishes for
                        the continuance of the friendly relations subsisting between the two
                        countries are fully appreciated and cordially reciprocated.</p>
                    <p>May God have Your Majesty in His safe and holy Keeping.</p>
                    <p>Your Good Friend,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                        </signed>.</closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>By the President: <lb/>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>. </p>
                        <lb/>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1914</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </postscript>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
